##Urban Shelters in the midst of the epidemic, housing the homeless

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

Workers disinfect the rooms at the Xiantao rescue station. Photo courtesy of interviewees

By Zhou Hang

Editor | Tao Ruogu

Small corners are also struggling with the epidemic, the city rescue stations (known as rescue management stations) is one of them. This is not always a high-profile place, housing the homeless, in the city plays an indispensable role in the pocket.

A sudden COVID-19 stopped some from returning home. The vagrancy and begging lifestyle and dirty hygiene habits put this group at a higher risk of infection than the general population. Moreover, many of them suffer from mental illness or mental retardation and are unable to fight the epidemic on their own. The living space is further squeezed, and the rescue station, which is still open, is the only place for them.

This Spring Festival, Lin Li (not his real name) and his colleagues at the Xiantao Aid Center canceled their vacation and worked on the front line every day, busy with disinfection and sterilization and the purchase of scarce supplies.

In this county-level city, less than 100 kilometers from Wuhan, what is the situation faced by the homeless during this special period? What new challenges do staff face and how do they respond to them?

Here's Lin's dictation:

We (relief station) is the civil affairs system below the public institutions, usually specialized in helping vagrants and beggars. There's been a sudden outbreak, and we're on a tight schedule.

Twenty-nine night, Xiantao "closed city" the first day, the police came to a person, patrol found the homeless, a man in his 50s. His eyes glazed over, he looked mentally deficient, and he had a sleeping jacket over his head, his hands in his pockets, his autumn clothes on his back, and a pair of cloth shoes on his feet. He had nothing on him. He could barely communicate.

And one of the psychopaths, also brought in by the police, in stable condition, no visible signs of mania, but communication revealed persecution complex. There's a risk of immediate hospitalization, so we'll put him in isolation for observation.

This is a dangerous time to be here. If we don't, we don't have a problem with the space. But when you don't take them in, where do they go? Where do they eat, where do they sleep.

A homeless man lives in a subway in Nanjing, Jiangsu Province, in February 2018. Graphics and text irrelevant

In the past, we would have a holiday and take turns on duty during the Spring Festival. Last year, on the third day of the Lunar New Year. Not this year, the first day of the first month in the afternoon, the station emergency meeting, cancel the vacation, all on duty. Now we have taken in nine, except for the two above, the rest are due to "closed city" can not go home.

On the third day of the first lunar month, an old gentleman came to me for help. Henan native, 59, Graying, plain looking and well dressed. He had a couple of thousand yuan on him, and he had planned to go home for the New Year twenty-nine, just in time for the "closure of the city. " . Before he should be in (part-time) the boss at the House for a few days, is not a long-term solution, they let him to the aid station to see. He was very upset when he came. He asked if we'd take it. Of course we'd take it.

There is a young man, 17 years old, four months old, working boy looks, dressed very fashionable, the Korean version of the jacket, carrying a suitcase, have no money. A few days ago by workers to help, now no place to go, Internet cafes are closed, wandering in the streets, the police brought us here.

The young man's hometown of Chongqing, probably because the third-party recruitment false propaganda, reported high wages, reported low labor intensity, to bear, worked for a month or two to leave, probation period did not pass, salary also can not get. He doesn't talk much, he doesn't contact his family, he doesn't give us his contact information. But he's got an ID, so when the traffic clears, we'll buy him a ticket and send him home.

Last year, we sent more than 20 people just like him back home. Well, we don't eat much here, but we're certainly not hungry enough. Come and take a shower. They need it. Clothes are free, winter hair down jacket, men's black, women's red.

The rescue station also has the rule, our semi-closed management, after coming can only in the rescue station activity, the room does not have the socket, the personal belongings including the cell phone needs to replace the safekeeping. You can call your family. You'll be notified if there's a call. Chongqing that young man these days estimates to hold also afflictive, but still quite cooperate with.

Help is on a voluntary basis. These days some people come over, we tell him the rules, feel unbearable, straight away.

We have an aid truck that goes out every day, especially to culverts, under bridges, but lately these places have been empty by day, and the city is empty. Well, there are a few people that wander around at night, and when the cops see them, they bring them to us. Public Security and urban management patrols found that in need of assistance, also have the responsibility of timely assistance.

To be honest, other places, like Yichang, are more detailed, constantly patrolling the streets, but we're outnumbered, only 24 hours a day.

Counting the orderlies, there were more than a dozen of us. One in his hometown can not come back, two were transferred to the village to supervise the epidemic prevention and control work, others are on duty, every night arrangements.

Duty Roster of Xiantao rescue stations during Spring Festival

Now in the downtown area, one person per household can go out every two days to shop. We go to and from work, have a unit to prove, but the car can not drive, general motor vehicles are banned, can only ride a bicycle to and from work. Home must be personal protection, disinfectant diluted spray clothes, cuffs, pants legs are sprayed again, take off the coat, drying in the balcony ventilation place.

Some time ago, when people came to the aid station, we would take their temperature to see if they had a cough, and then we would take them in. I used to use Mercury-in-glass thermometer. After the outbreak, a hospital sent us two new thermometers, infrared sensors, a head shot. Convenience is convenient, but may be the reason for the manufacturer gifts, quality is not good, often error, so can only use both.

It's the only health screening we have. The request is the rescue object must first check-up, no problem then sent into the station, but a period of time the situation is grim, fixed-point hospital is also few, no symptoms of the people in the hospital simply do not care. The strain on medical resources has eased somewhat.

The last two were found in a rural area, taken to the hospital for tests, chest x-rays, and sent here clean. One had been walking for a few days from Yichang, trying to get home to Jiangxi, where he said he was hungry and cold. We were all surprised when he told us about his experience.

People come in, we'll be isolated, three-person rooms for one person only. We have 48 beds, and since the minors'men's and women's quarters are empty, we can accommodate them. In the work as far as possible or avoid direct contact, eating on the door, they eat the bowl and chopsticks handed out.

Every day, we hand out masks to staff and new arrivals. Two A day, one in the morning and one in the afternoon. Except for the twenty-nine the police had brought in on the night of New Year's, the others had masks on, but only the old man in Henan had two spare ones in his bag, and no one else had more. I don't know what they're GONNA do if they don't come to the shelter.

We used to use masks. We had 500, ordinary disposable masks, $15 a pack, 50 a pack. On the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, we added 1,000 new ones, the ones that are packed separately, 3 yuan each, for 10 days and half a month, no problem.

But there's a shortage of disinfectant. We usually make a purchase once a month. Last purchase was after New Year's Day, 20 bottles of 84 disinfectants, 5 bottles of medical alcohol. Well, if we're still taking people in, we can't stop the decontamination. If one of our patients shows up, we could be wiped out.

At 7:00 in the morning, the paramedics go to work and sanitize their rooms. We used to kill them once a day, but now we do them in the morning, in the afternoon while they're active, and again in the evening. Other places, like work stations, have to be eliminated. The alcohol is mainly for the workers to go out and come back to sterilize the clothes with a watering can.

Xiantao aid workers do routine temperature and blood pressure tests on homeless people. Photo courtesy of the respondents

The outbreak came too suddenly to be fully prepared. Before January 22, all work or step-by-step, 23, "closed city" began, we looked everywhere disinfectant supplies, sold out, no channels to buy.

Xiantao is an important place for medical materials production, but even if the company runs 7 factories, it can not be purchased. As a result, the product can not be brought directly to Wuhan and some big hospitals.

On February 2nd, we ran out of disinfectant and alcohol, every last drop. And the Hazmat suits have never. It's too complicated. We need it for reception, security. We'll figure it out on our own. On February 3rd, through personal connections, they found a local supermarket, put in a good word, and they gave us 10 vials of 84 for our own use.

But if we economize, we'll only have five days. Fortunately, the next day, a friend unit is well-off, and the transfer of a little friendship, 20 bottles of disinfectant, 100 pairs of medical gloves, 10 protective clothing, it is a relief.

This day the city also set up a centralized trading point in the highway, can be fixed-point purchase of medical supplies. We do not have alcohol, disinfectant is not long enough to support, protective clothing is too little, originally intended to go to the headquarters to try to buy a batch, but said that only with the production contract units, there is no spot stall sales.

Later (Civil Affairs) bureau unified to the headquarters to obtain a batch of supplies, plus the China Social Welfare Foundation through the provincial department also allocated a batch, the issue of killing supplies was solved. But there's still a critical shortage of protective equipment.

When the traffic control is over, the station may arrange for a proper rest break. But until this epidemic is over, unless there's a medical condition that requires isolation, we will all be on duty, and we will continue to do our jobs.

We've got 30 more to go. When the Custody and repatriation was abolished in 2003 and replaced with a relief system, the vast majority of those left homeless were mentally and intellectually challenged. These people are away all the year round, and some families even think they have lost their Hukou. Some people can't get an ID from DNA or facial recognition.

The Guy who's in his twenty-nine, we did run facial recognition to his hometown, next county over. Recently, through the aid station, we learned that his family was looking for him, too. But roads are blocked everywhere, villages and villages are closed, and there's been a notice from above to stop picking each other up. Just stay here with us.

The first people who came here are now almost out of quarantine, no abnormal reactions, and we are gradually relieved. All nine of them are fine now.

Xiantao aid station.
